      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/29/5268",
      "text": [
        ": \"إِذَا قَتَلَ اَلْحُرُّ اَلْعَبْدَ غُرِّمَ قِيمَتَهُ وَ أُدِّبَ\" قِيلَ لَهُ فَإِنْ كَانَتْ قِيمَتُهُ عِشْرِينَ أَلْفاً قَالَ \"لاَ يُجَاوَزُ بِقِيمَةِ عَبْدٍ عَنْ دِيَةِ حُرٍّ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5268 - Abu Abdullah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said:\n\"If a free man kills a slave, he must pay the slave's value and be disciplined.\"\nIt was asked: \"What if the value of the slave is twenty thousand?\"\nImam (as) replied: \"The value of a slave cannot exceed the blood money (diyyah) of a free person.\""
        ]
      }
    },
